    "rationale": "The credibility assessment is accepted for submission purposes despite all seven assessed factors showing achieved levels below required levels and six factors flagged as not-assessed epistemic gaps. The provenance chain supporting the hemolysis claim includes the ancillary validation result (vr-hemolysis-ancillary-002) which is described as derived from prior experimental work; the upstream provenance linkage for this node was considered implicit by the review team and was not flagged during initial review. This constitutes the W-PROV-01 weakness: the ancillary result node has no prov:wasDerivedFrom, prov:wasGeneratedBy, or prov:used edge and is not marked as foundational evidence, leaving the chain dead-ended at non-foundational evidence.",
